Dynamic programming is an efficient way to solve problems involing recursion that have a following structure:
1. Overlapping subproblems: the solutions of subproblems are used multple times
2. Optimal substructure: the optimal solution of a problem is a function of the optimal solution of its subproblems.

Some examples of problems with optimal substructure: edit distance & longest common subsequence.

Dynamic programming arises in a variety of domains: sequence alignment in computational biology, ...
